I"Í<div class="p">Let reason strip the fineries of heart</div>
<div class="p">From fundaments of pain obscured by art;</div>
<div class="p">Let suffering regain its rightful place</div>
<div class="p">As the condition of our mortal race;</div>
<div class="p">Let massing sophistries of optimism,</div>
<div class="p">Confining life to routine mechanism,</div>
<div class="p">Let pipes and whistles of a noontime lark,</div>
<div class="p">Let definitions of a bounded dark,</div>
<div class="p">Let abrogations of man's mortal care,</div>
<div class="p">Let all the steaming billows of despair,</div>
<div class="p">Dissolve their vast oppressive weight,</div>
<div class="p">That man again may minister his fate.</div>
